00:30:21,482 --> 00:30:23,063
Does the vendor?

225
00:30:25,733 --> 00:30:29,437
maintain that data in any way besides just holding it?

226
00:30:29,718 --> 00:30:31,399
Is there any kind of, like, you wouldn't know?

227
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:37,406
I wouldn't think so, other than just maintaining the database and storing it.

228
00:30:38,307 --> 00:30:43,373
I don't know that it's stored in the same way that the LPR is stored, because I've never asked that of them.

229
00:30:46,570 --> 00:30:59,064
Yeah, if there's concerns about data being stored indefinitely, I just wanted to make people aware that the citation data is also stored indefinitely, as people who showed up for renewals and had tickets from 2016 that were unpaid found out.

230
00:30:59,705 --> 00:31:00,706
So, yeah.

231
00:31:02,267 --> 00:31:05,051
I just thought I'd mention that.

232
00:31:05,551 --> 00:31:05,751
Okay.

233
00:31:08,437 --> 00:31:10,418
I'm happy to come to another meeting to answer more questions.

234
00:31:10,498 --> 00:31:12,119
I myself just whipped this report together.

235
00:31:12,139 --> 00:31:21,846
I didn't really have time to review the surveillance policy I put together last year or the impact report from last year to see if there's been anything else I should mention.

236
00:31:22,266 --> 00:31:34,113
But yeah, folks can just reach out if they have questions to me, if they want to, about this policy or the use of the LPR or tickets or anything.

237
00:31:35,054 --> 00:31:35,774
Okay, thank you.

238
00:31:35,995 --> 00:31:36,335
Thank you.

239
00:31:42,357 --> 00:31:44,257
