252
00:33:18,185 --> 00:33:29,651
I think it makes sense to go back to the ordinance to look at what avenues we have, given I'm sure that folks have questions for the police.

253
00:33:31,772 --> 00:33:33,993
It might make sense to collect the questions

254
00:33:35,534 --> 00:33:39,135
in some form and send them over if we can't get them to schedule another meeting.

255
00:33:39,155 --> 00:33:42,795
But I think we should schedule another, try to schedule another meeting first.

256
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:46,656
Because it's best to get people in person and to ask those questions.

257
00:33:46,696 --> 00:33:51,597
So I would recommend trying to schedule that meeting first, keeping this paper in committee.

258
00:33:52,937 --> 00:33:54,877
I'll make that motion to keep the paper in committee.

259
00:33:57,178 --> 00:33:58,378
But it's frustrating.

260
00:33:58,578 --> 00:34:04,379
And I think it's important actually to have an opportunity where members of the public can ask questions.

261
00:34:05,970 --> 00:34:10,312
That's a huge part of the ordinance, alas.

262
00:34:14,013 --> 00:34:14,473
Thank you.

263
00:34:15,014 --> 00:34:16,734
