266
00:34:44,262 --> 00:34:45,803
I mean we'll be seeing the chief soon.

267
00:34:46,003 --> 00:34:47,284
We have to review his budget.

268
00:34:47,984 --> 00:34:50,086
So it's not like we won't have a conversation.

269
00:34:52,167 --> 00:34:54,889
I mean maybe we could do this then but I'd hate to.

270
00:34:55,009 --> 00:34:56,610
I'd hate to have to do it then.

271
00:34:57,611 --> 00:35:01,173
We could have done it tonight and then talked about his budget during that meeting.

272
00:35:02,034 --> 00:35:02,974
Anyway.

273
00:35:03,034 --> 00:35:03,975
Councilor Leming.

274
00:35:05,868 --> 00:35:16,733
Yeah, I'll second Councillor Singh's motion and repeat the general frustration that's been echoed here tonight.

275
00:35:17,094 --> 00:35:21,696
I don't even think it would necessarily have to be the chief of police himself and answer this.

276
00:35:21,756 --> 00:35:26,418
It could be the lieutenant that's indicated in the report that's in charge of this.

277
00:35:26,478 --> 00:35:28,459
Just really any representative.

278
00:35:29,580 --> 00:35:32,101
I could understand if there's a scheduling,

279
00:35:34,062 --> 00:35:50,749
mishap or something like that, but these meetings are a time for the public to see the Medford Police Department engage in transparency and just be there for the Q&A.

280
00:35:52,830 --> 00:36:13,916
I did have questions related to MPD's general understanding of this policy, since we did get an email from a resident who said that they were told something by a member of the MPD that seemed to misunderstand this ordinance.

281
00:36:13,936 --> 00:36:16,337
So I would like to clarify that.

282
00:36:16,357 --> 00:36:19,818
And also just general questions about what is

283
00:36:21,478 --> 00:36:22,539
what is in the report.

284
00:36:25,121 --> 00:36:47,498
Beyond that, generally speaking, I don't like to see the attitude that ordinances that are written by the legislative body are optional, which is an attitude that I've seen several members of the administration engage in and

285
00:36:50,050 --> 00:36:57,272
that's really not something that we should be seeing, both with these deadlines and with other ordinances that are written by this body.

286
00:36:57,332 --> 00:36:59,793
So yeah, I don't really see how we can

287
00:37:11,557 --> 00:37:16,606
continue this particular meeting without anybody to answer any questions about the report.

288
00:37:16,666 --> 00:37:19,792
So I would I would second Councilor Sang's motion.

289
00:37:20,132 --> 00:37:20,513
That's all.

290
00:37:22,537 --> 00:37:22,997
Thank you.

